MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Upper Reach of Conway River    Access via Route 615 in Rapidan Wildlife Management Area (RWMA).    Tag #: 213  Tag tree description: 14" DBH birch on left bank (looking downstream).

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Bootens Run.  This site is a tributary of the Conway River.  Site located just outside of Shenandoah National Park.    Tag #: 225  Tag tree description: 12" DBH birch tree on right bank (looking downstream).

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Devils Ditch    Tag #: 284  Tag tree description: 12" DBH sycamore on left bank (looking downstream) where trail (Route 667) crosses.    Tributary of Conway River, which comes in from the west.  Access via Route 615 in Rapidan Wildlife Management Area (RWMA).  Waders are advisable for this site because crossing of Conway River is required to reach Route 667 and the site.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Bush Mountain Stream    Tag #: 218  Tag tree: 8" DBH birch tree on right bank looking downstream, next to tulip poplar that is Shenandoah National Park boundary tree.    Small tributary of the Conway River.  Access through Rapidan Wildlife Management Area (RWMA).  Must cross Conway River by foot to get to site location.  Sample at or above Shenandoah National Park boundary.  Four wheel drive is recommended, although not essential.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Pocosin Hollow above Middle River Road and Conway River.    Site located downstream of GR10, 25 yards above Middle River Road bridge and about 50 yards upstream of Conway River confluence.      Tag #: 732  Tag tree: 18" DBH sycamore on right bank looking downstream (visible from Middle River Road bridge).

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Entry Run in located in the Rapidan Wildlife Management Area (RWMA)    Tag #: 619  Tag tree: 15" DBH sycamore on right bank, looking downstream

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: South River at Shenandoah National Park boundary.    Site is located on eastern side of Shenandoah National Park (SHEN), at boundary of Park and Rapidan Wildlife Management Area (RWMA).    This site is accessible via South River Falls Picnic Area and South River fire road.     Tag #: 800  Tree: 18" DBH poplar on left bank looking downstream, just above SHEN boundary.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Robinson River in White Oak Canyon above Tims River confluence.    Site located below first falls on White Oak Canyon Trail, and approximately 25 yards above Tims River.  Located near MA02.    Tag #: 701  Tag tree: Triple-trunked white birch tree on left bank, looking downstream.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Tims River at Whiteoak Canyon   (formerly known as Negro Run - name was changed in 2017)    Northeastern tributary of Robinson River in Whiteoak Canyon.  Tims River flows into Robinson River approximately 100 yards below first major falls on Whiteoak Canyon Trail.  Located near MA01.     Tag #: 799  Tag tree: Over 30" DBH poplar on right bank, looking downstream.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Ragged Run at Shenandoah National Park boundary.    Land is posted at parking area - should get permission from landowners before proceeding.  For 2021 decadal sampling, TU volunteers secured permission on the spot when neighbors came to see why they were there.  Suggest obtaining permission in advance in the future.    Large rock fence near tag tree.    Tag #: 710  Tag tree: 10" DBH locust tree on right bank looking downstream.  Tag tree has red blaze, indicating Park boundary.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Cedar Run above Robinson River in Whiteoak Canyon.      Western tributary of Robinson River.    Significant flooding and incision/scarring at site and below.  Below site, the stream becomes braided with multiple channels.  Very wide and deep channel from flooding in the past.    Tag #: 798  Tag tree: 25" DBH sycamore on left bank, looking downstream.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Berry Hollow, north of White Oak Canyon.    Northern tributary of Robinson River.    Evidence of flooding at stream site--high banks in some places with large boulders.      Tag #: 797  Tag tree: 25" DBH poplar on left bank (looking downstream), next to large rock.  Tag placed 12" above ground, on non-stream-facing side.  Upstream of large granite boulder, downstream of multiple tree falls.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Mill Prong fork of Rapidan River above Camp Hoover    This is one of two tributaries of the Rapidan River above Camp Hoover in Shenandoah National Park. Camp Hoover is located between the two tributaries just above where they converge to form the Rapidan River. Mill Prong (MA12) is the northern tributary. Laurel Prong (MA13) is the southern tributary.    Tag #: 712  Tag tree: 16" DBH birch on left bank, looking downstream.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Laurel Prong fork of Rapidan River above Camp Hoover    This is one of two tributaries of the Rapidan River above Camp Hoover in Shenandoah National Park. Camp Hoover is located between the two tributaries just above where they converge to form the Rapidan River. Mill Prong (MA12) is the northern tributary. Laurel Prong (MA13) is the southern tributary.    Sample site is just upstream of Prime Minister's cabin (see photo).  Possibly no tag currently at this site - old tags were: 24091, 612.  (Do not sample small intermittent tributary to Laurel Prong with tag # 711)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Tributary to Laurel Prong (MA13)    In 2021, it was determined that the coordinates for MA13 in the 2010 and 2021 VTSSS site folders were actually on a tributary to Laurel Prong.  This station MA13_TRIB was created for the samples collected at this tributary.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Rapidan River above Staunton River.    Upper reach of Rapidan River, about 25 yards above Staunton River confluence.    Tag #: 796  Tag tree: Twin-trunked poplar (about 18" DBH) on right bank, looking downstream.  Tag tree is approximately 20 feet off bank between trail and stream.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Robinson River in White Oak Canyon, upstream of Route 600 bridge crossing.      Site is visible from the Route 600 bridge over Robinson River, just past White Oak Canyon trail parking area.      Tag #: 709  Tag tree: 15" DBH sycamore on left bank looking downstream

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Fultz Run at Shenandoah National Park boundary.  Access via private property along small trail up to Shenandoah National Park (SHEN) boundary.    This is private property access.  Landowners must be contacted in advance to get permission to enter SHEN from their property. (In 2021 the Trout Unlimited coordinator Rodney Miner personally met with landowners one month before sampling time and secured permission.)     Landowner - Mr. K.R. Comer owns most of the land on Steam Hollow Road.  Address: 918 Steam Hollow Road. Phone: (540) 652-8752.   Landowner - Ms. Tammy Cave is the property owner at the very end of the road. Address: 978 Steam Hollow Road. Phone: (540) 742-2730.    Tag #: 733  Tag tree: Smaller of a double-trunked hemlock on right bank looking downstream.  2021 TU sample collectors could not locate tag tree (likely dead/down), but used tree with red blazes and SHEN fishing regulations sign seen in photos to locate site.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: East Branch of Naked Creek at Shenandoah National Park boundary    Upper tributary of Naked Creek.  Access via private property:  Landowner Information:  Mountaintop Ranch - Lydia Cunningham, owner       www.mountaintopranch.com  1030 Mountaintop Ranch Road, Elkton, VA 22827     Phone (main cabin) 540-298-2472     Phone (cell) 540-405-1154    Landowner is very difficult to contact as there is no cell service up there.  Texting may be a better option.  In 2021 TU coordinator Rodney Minor wrote a letter to ask for permission to access, and Lydia gave permission via text message some days later. He also made a personal visit to see Lydia prior to the sampling date to make sure where to go and highly recommends doing this before any visit.    Must walk upstream along stream bank above falls to find site.  Stream is approximately 10 feet wide at site.      Tag #: 731  Tag tree: Large (approximately 25" DBH) sycamore on right bank looking downstream, across from rock face with SHEN blazes.    NOTE:  PG09 (Big Creek) can be visited in conjunction with this site. It is further up Jollett Road and very close.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Big Creek at Shenandoah National Park boundary.    Tributary of Naked Creek.  Access via gravel road (Route 759) and then 0.5 mile hike on minimal trail.    Large boulders and slabs in river at site make for suitable sampling locations.  Site is located 0.5 mile upstream from residential development.      Tag #: 728 (new tag), 637 (existing tag)  Tag tree: Twin-trunked oak with Shenandoah National Park (SHEN) sign and orange blazes on right bank (looking downstream).  Old tag is nearly engulfed by bark.    NOTE:  PG08 (East Branch of Naked Creek) can be visited in conjunction with this site. It is accessed from Mountaintop Ranch Road, which is a turn off of Jollett Road.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Big Ugly Run.  Sample 25 yards above South Branch Naked Creek in Shenandoah National Park.    Access through private land - obtain permission in advance.  In 2021:  Owner of red house (1547 South Creek Road) is Mike Smith, who rents it out.  Contact at house is Barry Conrad Crawford (540-713-8150).  DO NOT go up driveway to right of this property - hostile landowner.    Tag #:727  Tag tree: 13" DBH chestnut oak on left bank looking downstream.  Fishing regulation sign on opposite bank.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Dry Run (lower) - Site is located above small pond.    Site access is through private property - obtain permission in advance.  Landowner: Alan Zigler PO Box 181 Timberville, VA 22853  Phone: 540-896-1159  Contact Alan prior to sampling to ask for permission to access his property. TU coordinator Rodney Miner obtained permission in 2021 and knows Alan personally. Rodney's contact number is 540-705-6784.    Do not attempt to access via Dry Run Trail. This is private property with numerous landowners.    Tag #: 624  Tag tree: 9" DBH cherry with red National Park blazes on left bank, looking downstream

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Staunton River at University of Virginia (UVA) gage    Staunton River is a tributary of the Rapidan River.  The site is approximately 100 yards upstream of the Staunton/Rapidan confluence.  Note that it is hard to see confluence from the Staunton River trail so look for cascade/waterfall to locate site.      Tag #: 796  Tag Location: On stilling well/gage platform on right bank (looking downstream)
